  "prompt": "Where did Sheldon Cooper get his PhD?",
  "response": "Sheldon Cooper, a fictional character from the television series **\"The Big Bang Theory\"** and its prequel **\"Young Sheldon,\"** earned his Ph.D. in **Theoretical Physics** from the **California Institute of Technology (Caltech)**. Remarkably, Sheldon completed his doctoral studies at the age of 16, showcasing his exceptional intellect and early academic achievements within the show's narrative.\n\n**Key Points:**\n- **Institution:** California Institute of Technology (Caltech)\n- **Field of Study:** Theoretical Physics\n- **Age at Completion:** 16 years old\n\nCaltech plays a central role in both series, serving as the primary workplace for Sheldon and his colleagues as they navigate their careers in science and academia.",
